Package fr.upmc.datacenter.hardware.processors.interfaces

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ProcessorDynamicStateI
    The interface ProcessorDynamicStateI gives access to the dynamic state information of processors transmitted by data interfaces of processors.
    ProcessorIntrospectionI
    The interface ProcessorIntrospectionI gives access to the state information of processors through offered ports of processors.
    ProcessorManagementI
    The interface ProcessorManagementI defines methods for the management (actuation) of a processor, such as modifying the frequency of cores.
    ProcessorServicesI
    The interface ProcessorServicesI defines the functional services of a processor, such as running a task on a given core.
    ProcessorServicesNotificationConsumerI
    The interface ProcessorServicesNotificationConsumerI is implemented by consumers of the processor notifications.
    ProcessorServicesNotificationI
    The interface ProcessorServicesNotificationI defines the notification services, namely the end of task notification.
    ProcessorStateDataConsumerI
    The interface ProcessorStateDataConsumerI defines the consumer side methods used to receive state data pushed by a processor, both static and dynamic.
    ProcessorStaticStateDataI
    The interface ProcessorStaticStateDataI defines the static state notification services for Processor components.
    ProcessorStaticStateI
    The interface ProcessorStaticStateI gives access to the static state information of processors transmitted by data interfaces of processors and computers.
